UCPRN05.PT51"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="part" searchtype="LEGISLATION PART" subdoc="false" toc-caption="PART 51 COURT OF APPEAL [rr 51.1&#x2013;51.61]"><leg:levelbody><leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT51.D8"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="division" searchtype="LEGISLATION DIVISION" subdoc="false" toc-caption="DIVISION 8 MISCELLANEOUS [rr 51.46&#x2013;51.61]"><leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT51.D8.SD4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subdivision" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBDIVISION" subdoc="false" toc-caption="Subdivision 4 Other [rr 51.57&#x2013;51.61]">
<leg:heading><desig searchtype="SUBDIV-NUM"><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT51.D8.SD4" type="ext"/>Subdivision 4</designum></desig><title searchtype="SUBDIV-TITLE">Other [rr 51.57&#x2013;51.61]</title></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-57"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 51.57] r 51.57 Hearing in fixed vacation (cf SCR Part 51, rule 52)">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-57" type="ext"/>[r 51.57]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Hearing in fixed vacation (cf SCR Part 51, rule 52)</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>51.57</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-57.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-57.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An application for an order that an appeal or other proceedings be heard during the fixed vacation must, unless the Court otherwise orders, be accompanied by:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-57.1.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-57.1.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>an affidavit showing the grounds on which the application is based, and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-57.1.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-57.1.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>a draft order.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<glp:note>
<heading><title>Note:</title></heading>
<p>
<text><remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05_R18-1" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID" status="unval">Rule 18.1</remotelink>
 requires an interlocutory or other application to a court to be made by motion unless the rules otherwise provide.</text></p></glp:note>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-57.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-57.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>The application may be dealt with by the Court in the absence of the public and without the attendance of any person.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-58"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 51.58] r 51.58 Review of order of Judge of Appeal (cf SCR Part 51, rule 56)">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-58" type="ext"/>[r 51.58]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Review of order of Judge of Appeal (cf SCR Part 51, rule 56)</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>51.58</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An application to the Court for the variation or discharge of an order of a Judge of Appeal must be made on notice of motion filed:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-58..A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-58..A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>within 14 days after the date on which the order is made, or</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-58..B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-58..B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>within such extended time as the Court may fix.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT51.R58.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.51-58-5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[51.58.5] Review of orders made by a single judge of appeal"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.51-58-5" type="ext"/>[51.58.5] </edpnum><title>Review of orders made by a single judge of appeal</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>This rule complements the provisions of SCA s 46. Under SCA s 46(1), a single judge of appeal can exercise various powers of the Court of Appeal in relation to, amongst other things, consent orders, dismissal for want of prosecution and directions. SCA s 46(4) permits the Court of Appeal to review any order made, or direction given, by a single judge of appeal in the exercise of that power.</text></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-59"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 51.59] r 51.59 Review of decisions of Registrar (cf SCR Part 61, rule 4)">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-59" type="ext"/>[r 51.59]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Review of decisions of Registrar (cf SCR Part 61, rule 4)</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>51.59</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-59.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-59.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A Judge of Appeal may exercise the powers of the Court under 
<remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT49" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Part 49</remotelink>
 to review a decision of the Registrar.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-59.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-59.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>This rule does not limit the powers of the Court to review decisions of the Registrar under 
<remotelink dpsi="05CC" refpt="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT49" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID">Part 49</remotelink>
.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 51.60] r 51.60 Application for expedited hearing">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60" type="ext"/>[r 51.60]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Application for expedited hearing</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>51.60</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>A party may apply for the hearing of proceedings in the Court to be expedited.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60.2"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60.2" type="ext"/>(2)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>An interested party may file a notice of non-objection to the hearing of the proceedings being expedited.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60.3"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60.3" type="ext"/>(3)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>If notices of non-objection are filed by each of the interested parties, the application may be decided in the absence of the public and the parties.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60.4"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60.4" type="ext"/>(4)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Reasons for a decision under subrule (3) need not be given.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60.5"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-60.5" type="ext"/>(5)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>This rule does not limit any other power of the Court to order that the hearing of proceedings be expedited.</text></p>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:bodytext>
<leg:histnote>
<p><text>[r 51.60  insrt Amendment 19 of 2007  r 3 and Sch 3[5], effective 1 January 2008]</text></p></leg:histnote>
<leg:comntry subdoc="true" toc-caption="NOTE"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><title><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.PT51.R60.COM1" type="ext"/>NOTE</title></heading>
<level id="UCPN_UCPR.SGM_UCPN.UCPR.51.60.5" leveltype="para0" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[51.60.5] Expedition in the Court of Appeal"><heading searchtype="COMMENTARY"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.51.60.5" type="ext"/>[51.60.5] </edpnum><title>Expedition in the Court of Appeal</title></heading>
<bodytext searchtype="COMMENTARY">
<p>
<text>The hearing of an appeal may be expedited in an appropriate case. Whether it is appropriate will depend upon a number of considerations and will depend upon the circumstances of the particular case. Although there are no inflexible rules as to when expedition will be granted, certain situations present obviously strong claims for expedition. These include, but are not limited to: (i) cases involving personal liberty; (ii) cases involving the welfare of children; (iii) cases where, at least in the absence of a stay, delay would render the appeal practically futile, even if it was legally successful; (iv) cases involving irreparable loss or hardship: <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="1995"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr012716" spanref="cr012716-001"><ci:reporter value="NSWLR"/><ci:volume num="38"/><ci:page num="395"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr012717" spanref="cr012717-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC9506831"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Elders Rural Finance Ltd v Smith</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr012716-001">(1995) 38 NSWLR 395</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr012717-002"> BC9506831</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="131720" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>; discussing with approval the expedition guidelines set out in <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr012718" spanref="cr012718-001"><ci:reporter value="All ER"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1995"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="587"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr012719" spanref="cr012719-002" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="WLR"/><ci:volume num="1"/><ci:edition><ci:date year="1995"/></ci:edition><ci:page num="243"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Unilever plc v Chefaro Propietaries Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr012718-001">[1995] 1 All ER 587</ci:span>; <ci:span spanid="cr012719-002" status="unval">[1995] 1 WLR 243</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="84024" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>. Examples include:</text>
<l>
<li>
<lilabel>&#x2022;</lilabel>
<p><text>risk of loss of livelihood see <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseinfo><ci:decisiondate year="2008"/></ci:caseinfo><ci:caseref ID="cr012720" spanref="cr012720-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="IR"/><ci:volume num="176"/><ci:page num="426"/></ci:caseref><ci:caseref ID="cr012721" spanref="cr012721-002"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC200809151"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Hannaford v Cactus Imaging Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> <ci:span spanid="cr012720-001" status="unval">(2008) 176 IR 426</ci:span>; [2008] NSWCA 260; <ci:span spanid="cr012721-002"> BC200809151</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="464731" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>, McColl JA (expedition not opposed but no consent &#x2014; application granted); </text></p></li>
<li>
<lilabel>&#x2022;</lilabel>
<p><text>risk of increased costs as a result of duplication and delay: see <ci:cite searchtype="CASE-REF"><ci:case><ci:caseref ID="cr012722" spanref="cr012722-001" status="unval"><ci:reporter value="urj"/><ci:refnum num="BC201203111"/></ci:caseref></ci:case><ci:content><citefragment searchtype="CASE-NAME-REF"><emph typestyle="it">Moorebank Recyclers Pty Ltd v Tanlane Pty Ltd</emph></citefragment><citefragment searchtype="CASE-CITE-REF"> [2012] NSWCA 115; <ci:span spanid="cr012722-001" status="unval"> BC201203111</ci:span></citefragment> <remotelink dpsi="0018" refpt="552858" remotekey1="REFPTID" service="DOC-ID"><inlineobject alttext="Click for CaseBase entry" attachment="web-server" filename="cbcc.gif" type="image"/></remotelink></ci:content></ci:cite>, McColl JA (expedition not opposed &#x2014; costs related to development application).</text></p></li></l></p>
</bodytext>
</level></leg:comntry>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
</leg:level>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-61"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="rul" searchtype="LEGISLATION RUL" subdoc="true" toc-caption="[r 51.61] r 51.61 Affidavits in support of orders sought by notice of motion">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><edpnum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-61" type="ext"/>[r 51.61]</edpnum><title searchtype="RUL-TITLE">Affidavits in support of orders sought by notice of motion</title><desig searchtype="RUL-NUM"><designum>51.61</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:level id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-61.1"><leg:level-vrnt leveltype="subrul" searchtype="LEGISLATION SUBRUL">
<leg:levelinfo>
<leg:levelstatus isrepealed="false" ln.user-displayed="false"/></leg:levelinfo>
<leg:heading inline="true"><desig><designum><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-61.1" type="ext"/>(1)</designum></desig></leg:heading>
<leg:levelbody>
<leg:bodytext>
<p><text>Unless the Court orders otherwise:</text></p>
<l><li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-61.1.A"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-61.1.A" type="ext"/>(a)</lilabel>
<p><text>a party that files a notice of motion must also file an affidavit setting out the evidence that the party relies on in support of the orders sought by the notice, and</text></p>
</li>
<li id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-61.1.B"><lilabel><refpt id="UCPN.UCPR.UCPRN05.R51-61.1.B" type="ext"/>(b)</lilabel>
<p><text>a party that opposes an order sought by a notice of motion must file an affidavit setting out the evidence that the party relies on in opposition to the order.</text></p>
</li>
</l>
</leg:bodytext>
</leg:levelbody>
</leg:level-vrnt>
